metadata.name: FXHASH Generative Logo #541
metadata.description:
Unique iteration of the first Generative Token minted on fxhash.

It also servers as the actual logo of the platform. It represents the generative processes driving fxhash tokens. Generative Tokens are fed with a unique hash to produce unique outputs based on the hash — they are functions with a hash as single input.

The growth that comes out of the text is driven by a "Dividing-Aggregating Walkers" (DAW) algorithm. The hash drives all the DAW settings, as well as a mutation factor which is responsible for changes in each Walker parameters as they divide.

Some iterations will produce very simple outputs whereas others might be more chaotic.

Piece by @ciphrd for fxhash

metadata.name: Charcoal Brutalism #49
metadata.description:
Based on a similar technique as "Charcoal Landscapes", using lines limited to 8 possible directions, this work is about the repetition of patterns at different scales and the use of negative spaces.
The texture created from the noise combined with the structures that emerges from this algorithm create a look similar to the brutalist architecture of the last century.

There are 10 scale variations but with almost infinite possible outcomes.
Inverted colours have a small chance of dropping.

Original artwork by William Watkins · Lyon, 2022

metadata.name: Act One #314
metadata.description:
Act One, where the mannequin says “take me home and I will dance for you forever”.

This work is an exploration of using motion capture data to create digital paintings, and a little belated birthday ballet for #fxhashturnsone. 
20% of primary sales are donated to Three.js.
 
Keyboard Controls:
[P] Play / pause the dance. By default the dance is paused after a few seconds to render a painting.
[S] Save the current view (live mode).
[V] Capture a short webm video (live mode).

Mouse Controls (while dancing): 
[left drag] Rotate
[scroll] Zoom
[right drag] Pan
[right click] Save image

Best viewed in a desktop browser. The output may be different from the preview image if your frame rate is low, reducing the size of the browser window can help improve the frame rate.

Made using Three.js, canvas API and WebGL2.
The 3D model is based on https://sketchfab.com/3d-models/mannequin-dances-ballet-a24678a81a6f4b6d8f8ba0eb1a78e58b, using motion capture data from dancedb.eu. 
Test in Chrome v107.0.5304.107 and Safari v16.1.
License: CC BY-NC-SA 2.0

Created by elsif, 2022.11.

metadata.name: Cradle #334
metadata.description:
Billions of years old, ancient remains decay across our Solar System. Mere transient visitors to our star, their ephemeral presence on our worlds is embodied in their creations. In the shadow of their megalithic constructions, we wonder what they might have brought to us.

They brought life.

----

Live mode controls:
'r' - change resolution
's' - save PNG
'f' - render at full speed
'space' - stop/continue rendering

The image quality gradually improves over time. The rendering speed is reduced by default - press 'f' for the maximum speed.

Rendering may be GPU intensive.

metadata.name: Quantum Folly #294
metadata.description:
This piece explores humanity's vanity and obsession with controlling natural forces. In the end we are beholden to the whims of the universe and its rules. What we think is artificial is but nature's inclination.

As an atom gazes at the world it can see the arrogant hand of mankind imposing its will. We are nature's inane creation built from imperceptible, discrete particles.

Enjoy watching the structures form. Due to the nature of the system it may take some time to complete. Once it's fully rendered you can download a full resolution image of 3508 x 4961 px by ***double clicking/tapping***. At this size the piece is printable at A3 size at 300 dpi. If you're interested in acquiring a signed print please contact @KRANKARTA.

Features include: palette, orientation, architecture, particle rules, boundary seepage and colour displacement.

Created on Chrome desktop 103.0 on 2022-07-21 in javascript and GLSL. Results on other browsers/devices may vary.

metadata.name: Shattered Moons #309
metadata.description:
🌘🌗🌖Shattered Moons🌔🌓🌒

Explore deep space moons through this pure SVG generative experiment.

Features:
- Striped Background
- Shadows
- Vapors
- Horizontal Vapors
- Meteors
- Colored Meteors
- White Moon (0.5%)

SVG being a vectorial format, this work can be displayed/printed at any size.
Press 's' on Live View to save the SVG.
Press 'p' on Live View using a Chromium based browser to export as PNG.

Also, to fully enjoy your piece, I'd suggest to use a Chromium based browser as the SVG renderer gives more details.

metadata.name: RGB Elementary Cellular Automaton #905
metadata.description:
Stephen Wolfram's Elementary Cellular Automaton where 3 different rules are drawn in the Red, Green and Blue color components of the image.

Rules are selected randomly among a pre-selection of 53 rules from which nice behaviors emerge.

Tokens can have a cell size in the [1; 20] range.
